headline: Akamai Stock Slides After Earnings. ‘Stay the Course,’ Analysts Say.
summary: Shares of  Akamai Technologies  plummeted Friday after the cloud-services company beat earnings expectations but forecast an uptick in capital spending in 2026.  Late Thursday,  Akamai  posted adjusted earnings of $1.84 a share for the fourth quarter, ahead of the $1.76 analysts had anticipated, according to FactSet.  Capital expenditures will weigh on earnings in 2026, the company said, estimating that capex will be 23% to 26% of revenue for the year, up from 19% in 2025.
